Say you wanted to add a permission for every project in the system.  This would be a good place to use Jelly, except that the <jira:SelectProjectScheme> requires the permission scheme name, and presumably you only have the project key/name.  Nor can you look up the permission scheme name, as there isn't a tag.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
