While you're editing a find-issues query, the form does a post to a search results page.  The problem is this is that it creates an annoying "Do you want to resubmit your POST" if you use your browser back button to return to it.

If the form POST response was to redirect to the search page so that the browser then hit that as a GET, then you could set all the session search criteria you wanted, and still return the find issues results nicely, and no more back arrow problems.

Browser Message in FireFox:
{panel}
The page you are trying to view contains POSTDATA that has expired from cache. If you resend the data, any action the form carried out (such as a search or online purchase) will be repeated. To resend the data, click OK. Otherwise, click Cancel.
{panel}

